{
  "text": "Bnding length of fabric samples was measured as per standard protocol of ASTM D-1388 on a cantilever, crease recovery angle (CRA) as per standard protocol of ISO 2313 and tensile strength as per standard protocol of ASTM D-5034. The bacterial strains of Escherichia coli and Staphylococcus aureus were employed to estimate the antibacterial activity of treated samples as per documented earlier [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "93928038"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "93928038": {
      "title": "Performance enhancement of wool fabric with environmentally-friendly bio cross-linker",
      "abstract": "Abstract In this research, an environmentally-friendly cross-linker, citric acid, has been examined to enhance the resistance of wool to relaxation shrinkage. Citric acid was not only helpful to reduce the relaxation shrinkage after washing but dry easy care performance was also enhanced. The incorporation of formic acid as swelling agent further enhanced the performance of citric acid on wool fabric. In addition, improvement of tensile strength and antimicrobial activity were other positive aspects of the cross-linking of wool with citric acid."
    }
  }
}